  "response_text": "**Moral Dilemma:**\n\nA doctor, Dr. Smith, is faced with a difficult decision. Two patients, John and Emily, are in critical condition in the hospital. John is a 35-year-old father of two young children, and Emily is a 25-year-old single mother of a 5-year-old child. Both patients have been involved in a severe car accident and require a liver transplant to survive. However, there is only one liver available, and it cannot be split into two portions to save both patients.\n\n**Option 1: Save John**\n\nIf Dr. Smith chooses to save John, he will be saving the life of a father who has a family that depends on him. John's children are young and still in school, and his wife is pregnant with their third child. Saving John would ensure that his family will have a breadwinner and a father figure to care for them.\n\n**Option 2: Save Emily**\n\nIf Dr. Smith chooses to save Emily",
